  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookEmbeddingService.cs:28-30` — capture current embed-input composition shape exactly.</step>
    <step order="2">Add a tolerant JSON parse helper that reads `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata` from the playbook entity and returns `(documentTypes, intents, triggerPhrases)` arrays (empty arrays on null / malformed JSON).</step>
    <step order="3">Extend the embed-input string composition: existing 4 sources + the 3 new arrays joined consistently (e.g., comma-separated within each section, newline between sections).</step>
    <step order="4">Add unit tests for: (a) baseline composition with no JPS metadata; (b) full JPS metadata composition; (c) malformed JSON tolerance; (d) partial JPS metadata (only `documentTypes`).</step>
    <step order="5">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` + `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`.</step>
    <step order="6">Measure BFF publish size: `dotnet publish -c Release ... -o deploy/api-publish/`; report delta.</step>
    <step order="7">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5 (code-review + adr-check).</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 032 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PlaybookEmbeddingService.cs + tests directory</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply changes + add tests</tool>
